data.value: The main window of the program can be divided into 3 parts: 1. Model parameters. In this part, the main parameters of the computer model are set: the size of the community, the initial number of "adherents" of I1 and I2, the coefficients of the intensity of the distribution of I1 and I2 along the internal and external channels. 2. Graph. In this area, the result is graphically interpreted. The graph plots information propagation curves for I1 and I2. 3. Area with the results of the program. In this area, the conclusion drawn from the simulation results for the entered parameters is presented. To demonstrate the features of the program, an example and an exercise are presented.

data.name: textBox16.Text
data.value: The computer model can be used to simplify the process of analyzing information war and to determine characteristics, the management of which can stimulate the course of the fight in the direction necessary for the participant. The developed model allows you to set the parameters of the social community (the number, the initial number of "adherents" of I1 and I2) and the characteristics of the spread of information flows (the coefficients of the intensity of the spread of I1 and I2 through internal and external channels). Based on this information, the user can obtain the following information: 1. The dynamics of the development of information war over time, i.e. the number of "adherents" of I1 and I2 at a particular time; 2. The end result of the war is the "winner", i.e. one who has managed to spread his information among a larger number of members of the community than the rival.
